W. T. SPENCER. CHIEF OF BUREAU

STATE OF NEBRASKA DEPARTMENT OF AGRICULTURE Bureau of Animal Industry Lincoln, Nebr., February 1st, 1920. Federal regulations governing the interstate movement .of cattle requiring the tuberculin test provide that the veterina - rian making the test must have the approval of the proper State Live Stock Sanitary Official, and the Chief of the United States Bureau of Animal Industry. The list of veterinarians submitted herewith has been properly approved. It includes all who, to date, are recognized as qualified to do Tuberculin and Mallein testing as well as all kinds of live stock inspection within the State. W. T Spencer, Chief of Bureau. Approved Leo Stuhr, Secretary of Agriculture.
